{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She saw the British army marching.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she lived to see the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But she died two days later of typhoid.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I think that was the cruelest blow God had ever dealt me and my sister.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because one was prepared for the worst, but we were given back our mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And yet before we could even meet, she was taken away without seeing us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the very next day, we had a letter from a completely unknown person to say that as far as they knew, our father had been shot on a death march at the end of 1944.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Nevertheless, I was determined to go back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "First of all, by then, I knew my aunt, mother's sister, had survived and was there, and that she had been with my mother most of those awful years.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I wanted to learn everything I could about their fate and fate of the other members of our family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Also, I mean, I was brought up in the Czech school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We were brought up to go back to our homeland to help to rebuild it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There was no thought of me staying.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And though both the Rainfords and Auntie Marjorie, even my bossy Auntie Marjorie, wanted to adopt me and wanted me to stay, there was no other thought in my head than to go back.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Eva couldn't go back at the same time, because she was taking her finals in a few months time, her nursing finals, and-- finals, and it seemed sensible in view of the fact that our parents hadn't survived that she should do those before contemplating a return.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went in a special plane.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a war plane adopted for taking kids back again.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
